-It turns out teaching is much harder, 
the prep and everything.   

00:38:16.110 --> 00:38:19.920
but you learn more from your students
 than they learn from you,  

00:38:19.920 --> 00:38:22.780
in my opinion. That’s real.   

00:38:22.780 --> 00:38:25.630
Oh, so what my professor, 
Bu Nila, said was true, huh?   

00:38:25.630 --> 00:38:27.460
-Absolutely, I really relate to that.   

00:38:27.460 --> 00:38:29.790
-She said learning doesn’t 
 have to come from professors.  

00:38:29.790 --> 00:38:31.790
 I also learn from listening 
 to all of you.   

00:38:31.790 --> 00:38:35.150
-I completely, completely agree with that.  

00:38:35.460 --> 00:38:39.240
 -So, to raise IQ I think the challenge 
 comes in three parts:   

00:38:39.980 --> 00:38:44.660
ourselves, our environment, 
 and lastly, the government.   

00:38:46.200 --> 00:38:52.160
First, I say it starts with us, 
 personally, it’s about habits.   

00:38:52.880 --> 00:38:55.480
We lack the habit of reading.   

00:38:56.900 --> 00:39:02.820
We lack reading habits because 
we lack libraries in schools.   

00:39:03.430 --> 00:39:06.480
And reading is associated 
 with academic books.   

00:39:07.120 --> 00:39:11.710
In my opinion not others’, 
just mine, disclaimer

00:39:12.150 --> 00:39:16.340
The books that should be read from an early age 
are not academic books at home,   

00:39:18.070 --> 00:39:19.480
but books of knowledge.  

00:39:20.160 --> 00:39:22.180
Because that’s what I do with my child.   

00:39:22.750 --> 00:39:26.500
And reading books today doesn’t have to 
mean physical books, there are e-books.   

00:39:27.150 --> 00:39:29.180
Give them books on an iPad, 
not just YouTube.   

00:39:29.320 --> 00:39:33.560
If the kid doesn’t want to read, then
 give them scientific content on YouTube.   

00:39:33.780 --> 00:39:39.630
Because books tell stories. If they’re 
 still in kindergarten, then comics or fairy tales. 

00:39:39.630 --> 00:39:44.000
The more often they read, what’s 
developed in their minds   

00:39:44.000 --> 00:39:46.790
is continuity in critical thinking.   

00:39:47.310 --> 00:39:50.800
Why did this happen? 
It happened because of this.   

00:39:50.800 --> 00:39:53.710
Why are our kids like this?   

00:39:53.710 --> 00:39:57.070
Because they’re used to memorizing,
 not thinking critically.   

00:39:57.390 --> 00:39:58.960
That’s what I’ve criticized 
from the beginning.   

00:39:59.710 --> 00:40:03.870
My privilege at Kanisius Elementary, a Catholic 
school, was that I wasn’t told to memorize.   

00:40:04.320 --> 00:40:08.480
I was told to understand. Shoutout to 
 Kanisius, Pangudi Luhur, and Ursulin.   

00:40:08.480 --> 00:40:10.630
Not saying others don’t do this.   

00:40:10.990 --> 00:40:13.380
Among Muslims there’s Muhammadiyah 
 and Insan Cendekia. 

00:40:13.380 --> 00:40:16.800
The folks at Insan Cendekia are extraordinary.
 All of them are geniuses.   

00:40:16.800 --> 00:40:21.670
So from what I see, proper high schools, 
be they Islamic, Catholic, Christian, or whatever,   

00:40:21.980 --> 00:40:26.660
they make students understand, 
not just memorize.   

00:40:27.680 --> 00:40:28.590
That’s number one.   

00:40:29.460 --> 00:40:31.950
Environment. Now this part,   

00:40:31.950 --> 00:40:34.100
my privilege is that my parents 
were educators.   

00:40:34.800 --> 00:40:35.360
-That’s amazing.  

00:40:35.360 --> 00:40:40.790
That’s something I can’t expect 
 from every family.  

00:40:40.790 --> 00:40:44.230
So this second point may 
 or may not be doable.   

00:40:44.800 --> 00:40:50.640
But I’ll offer this suggestion to 
parents with Gen Alpha kids.   

00:40:50.640 --> 00:40:54.400
That means parents in my generation, 
or your kid’s generation maybe.  

00:40:54.400 --> 00:41:00.200
 Those born after 2010.  
 Or, after 2014.   

00:41:00.630 --> 00:41:05.070
So now they’re around  
 10 years old. Talk to them.   

00:41:05.520 --> 00:41:07.560
Why? Because your kids—  

00:41:08.280 --> 00:41:13.270
just because they’re children doesn’t 
mean they don’t understand.   

00:41:13.620 --> 00:41:16.230
The difference between kids and 
adults in medical terms is

00:41:16.230 --> 00:41:21.620
kids can’t respond yet, but  they
 understand what we say.   

00:41:23.030 --> 00:41:29.430
So if you talk to a baby, they  
 understand what you’re saying.   

00:41:29.790 --> 00:41:34.980
And children are copycats 
of those closest to them.   

00:41:35.740 --> 00:41:39.510
So if your kid swears a lot, it clearly 
comes from the parents.  

00:41:40.380 --> 00:41:44.360
 If the parents aren’t around, then  
 it’s their circle. Kids are copycats.   

00:41:45.460 --> 00:41:51.430
So, talk to them, and because 
kids are super curious,   

00:41:52.140 --> 00:41:56.120
let them know where your money 
 comes from. 

00:41:57.380 --> 00:42:01.840
What changed me in elementary school was 
when my parents took me to their office.   

00:42:02.760 --> 00:42:06.240
So I knew what my mom and dad 
 were doing to earn money.   

00:42:06.550 --> 00:42:08.820
That’s what I’m doing  
 with my kid now.   

00:42:09.640 --> 00:42:12.540
I take my kid to the office, 
 "Look, this is what your dad does."  

00:42:12.540 --> 00:42:15.350
"When I’m at the hospital, this 
is how doctors work."   

00:42:16.180 --> 00:42:21.280
And eventually it helps them understand  
 that life requires money.   

00:42:21.280 --> 00:42:24.590
And the kid will feel respected  
because you talk to them often.  

00:42:24.590 --> 00:42:27.700
So they learn vocabulary 
  from their parents.   

00:42:27.700 --> 00:42:33.430
Now, what I see in some parenting styles,  
 "Have you studied? Do your homework!"   

00:42:35.950 --> 00:42:39.070
"Ugh, you’re so annoying! Dad’s
 tired from work, be quiet!"   

00:42:39.860 --> 00:42:43.390
So kids don’t get a chance  
 to talk. What’s the result?   

00:42:43.390 --> 00:42:46.240
When they grow up, they won’t 
  have the courage to speak up.   

00:42:46.240 --> 00:42:49.550
That’s why not all Indonesian
 kids become storytellers, Sir.   

00:42:49.550 --> 00:42:52.440
Because even in their own families  
they aren’t given the chance to talk.   

00:42:52.440 --> 00:42:56.720
They say a word and it’s, "Always arguing! 
You’re a disrespectful child!"   

00:42:56.720 --> 00:42:59.360
When they were just starting to talk...  

00:43:00.200 --> 00:43:03.880
So kids, because they still can't
 tell right from wrong,   

00:43:03.880 --> 00:43:05.910
they're very vocal, innocent.   

00:43:06.350 --> 00:43:10.030
It happened to my friend's kid   

00:43:10.590 --> 00:43:14.820
"Is this the uncle who always says weird stuff, 
like 'jancok-jancok' on YouTube?"   

00:43:15.300 --> 00:43:16.070
Whoa, dang.   

00:43:16.070 --> 00:43:21.720
After that, I started covering my tattoos because
 my friends’ kids were starting to criticize me.   

00:43:22.470 --> 00:43:26.080
It showed up on TikTok, "Mr. Tirta, Mr. Tirta, 
your hair used to be pink."  

00:43:27.230 --> 00:43:30.600
I didn’t think much of it before, but 
turns out I was influencing them.   

00:43:31.320 --> 00:43:32.580
So, that’s number two.   

00:43:33.460 --> 00:43:37.472
Number three, if we’ve already got number 
one, which is the habit of reading, 

00:43:37.470 --> 00:43:40.128
family environment, and government.   

00:43:41.430 --> 00:43:45.080
What’s most important from the government
 is to change our education system  

00:43:45.080 --> 00:43:48.680
not just chasing rankings or whatever, 

00:43:48.680 --> 00:43:53.110
but making sure education quality
is equal across the board. 

00:43:53.110 --> 00:43:56.980
Whatever the method, I believe the experts know,

00:43:56.980 --> 00:43:59.230
PhDs, policymakers.   

00:43:59.230 --> 00:44:04.180
But from my experience giving guest lectures, 

00:44:04.760 --> 00:44:08.080
the quality of education is still all over the place. 

00:44:12.870 --> 00:44:17.550
As long as we’re still comparing public and private schools, Java and Papua, 

00:44:17.790 --> 00:44:20.560
the gap of knowledge is going to be huge. 

00:44:21.320 --> 00:44:24.540
If we want to move forward as a country 
and aim for the golden generation in 2045, 

00:44:24.540 --> 00:44:27.420
the budget should be used to 
level out education quality 

00:44:27.420 --> 00:44:29.580
from Sabang to Merauke. That’s it, problem solved. 

