gets elected 

00:44:44.740 --> 00:44:48.400
and their focus is human capital, the 
results will only be seen 12 years 

00:44:48.400 --> 00:44:50.400
later when those kids graduate high school. 

00:44:51.720 --> 00:44:53.040
The one started won’t see the outcome. 

00:44:53.630 --> 00:44:57.780
It’ll be the president after them 
who reaps the benefits.

00:44:57.780 --> 00:45:02.580
If they serve two terms, 10 years, they’ll still 
be the ones building the foundation. 

00:45:03.190 --> 00:45:06.390
If we focus on human capital, 
the results will be clear. 

00:45:06.390 --> 00:45:09.700
Look at Japan, Korea, Finland, Europe,
they invested in people. 

00:45:09.700 --> 00:45:14.700
But the impact isn’t immediate. 
It takes 12 years. 

00:45:15.080 --> 00:45:17.270
Now, do we have the guts to
 stay committed to that? 

00:45:17.910 --> 00:45:21.740
That’s what I talk about
with friends in politics. 

00:45:22.670 --> 00:45:26.280
It’s hard, because it’s not something you 
can turn into a quick campaign promise. 

00:45:26.280 --> 00:45:32.980
People judge a leader’s success
 by what they can see.

00:45:33.510 --> 00:45:36.700
And education? It’s not visible. 

00:45:37.240 --> 00:45:40.510
Tangible projects are easier to 
sell, you can touch them, see them. 

00:45:40.510 --> 00:45:45.960
Education is an intangible investment. You’ll only 
see the results 12 years down the road. 

00:45:45.960 --> 00:45:51.740
Now, if point number two is met, but
 point three isn’t, you’ll have a mismatch.

00:45:52.340 --> 00:45:56.060
Some people will have an IQ of 140,
 others will be down at 50. 

