they carry heavy mental burdens
 but don’t talk about it.  

01:18:49.360 --> 01:18:52.400
They’re used to bottling it up.    

01:18:52.400 --> 01:18:59.050
They spend time fishing, going on solo 
trips, doing umrah multiple times,   

01:18:59.390 --> 01:19:03.680
or staying at the mosque for a long time 
 because that’s where they can “talk”.

01:19:03.680 --> 01:19:05.690
They’re just not used to speaking openly.     

01:19:05.690 --> 01:19:06.800
They are both different. 

01:19:07.560 --> 01:19:09.580
- Does that help reduce cortisol?   

01:19:09.580 --> 01:19:11.580
- It actually increases it, Pak.    

01:19:11.880 --> 01:19:12.750
-Instead?
-Yes. 

01:19:12.750 --> 01:19:18.650
That’s why many Gen X folks by 40, even if they 
exercise, they still suffer from heart issues. 

01:19:19.180 --> 01:19:21.020
That’s from work stress.   

01:19:21.550 --> 01:19:26.090
Their coworkers push them, 
“Come on, play football! You’re weak!”   

01:19:26.090 --> 01:19:27.520
Then, heart problems.   

01:19:27.520 --> 01:19:33.560
 So in my opinion, men over 40  
 carry incredibly high work stress.   

01:19:33.560 --> 01:19:36.380
Both men and women.     

01:19:36.380 --> 01:19:38.620
-How do we reduce cortisol?    

01:19:39.600 --> 01:19:41.820
-Stress release. Finding peace.   

01:19:42.480 --> 01:19:45.480
Through spirituality, or meditation,
 both active and passive.   

01:19:45.480 --> 01:19:49.880
I asked a meditation expert.   

01:19:50.380 --> 01:19:54.400
The first type is active: exercise, 

01:19:54.400 --> 01:19:59.130
yoga, pilates, hiking, eating.   

01:19:59.500 --> 01:20:06.680
The second is passive: praying, or 
traditional meditation like in Bali.   

01:20:06.990 --> 01:20:11.630
That’s okay too.  I can’t expect Gen X, 

01:20:11.630 --> 01:20:13.760
who are 10 years older than me, 
to open up.

01:20:13.760 --> 01:20:16.320
It’s hard to get them to talk.   

01:20:16.320 --> 01:20:17.920
They really don’t want to.   

01:20:19.340 --> 01:20:23.500
Most of them DM me anonymously to vent.  

01:20:23.500 --> 01:20:25.480
Their kids are already grown.   

01:20:25.710 --> 01:20:28.280
Their stress usually revolves 
around work or their kids.    

01:20:28.680 --> 01:20:33.880
"Doc, what do I do? My kid doesn’t want
 to go to college. I’m so stressed.”   

01:20:33.880 --> 01:20:36.040
That’s the kind of stuff they say, 
but never out loud.   

01:20:36.040 --> 01:20:40.640
That’s why their health issues aren’t far from 
diabetes, stroke, and heart disease.    

01:20:40.640 --> 01:20:44.640
Even if they don’t smoke or anything,
 it’s work stress.    

01:20:44.640 --> 01:20:48.030
Now why is Gen Z’s suicide rate increasing?   
Stress from anxiety.   

01:20:48.440 --> 01:20:52.620
 It’s overwhelming, isn’t it, Pak? Imagine being 
a psychiatrist with two massive patient groups.   

01:20:52.620 --> 01:20:58.480
Millennials? We act like we’re tough. Because we’re in
 our most productive years right now.

01:20:58.990 --> 01:21:09.420
28 to 38, we’re in our peak career phase.  
 So we tend to power through things.      

01:21:10.250 --> 01:21:14.600
-I’ve been meditating for the past 10 years.   

01:21:14.600 --> 01:21:18.410
So every morning, after dawn prayers,
 I meditate.  

01:21:19.290 --> 01:21:22.730
It really helps reduce cortisol.    

